## Performance Support as Behavior Change Tool

Performance support — job aids, checklists, 
decision trees, reference tools — is often 
more effective for behavior change than 
formal training, because it works at 
the moment of performance.

### When Performance Support Beats Training
- The behavior is infrequent and 
  forgetting between uses is inevitable
- The task is complex enough to require 
  reference even by experienced performers
- The consequence of error is high 
  and the stakes justify the support
- The barrier is remembering, not knowing

### Designing Effective Performance Support
- Make it accessible at the point of need
- Keep it as brief as possible
- Design it for use under pressure — 
  clear, scannable, unambiguous
- Test it with actual performers 
  in actual conditions
- Update it when procedures change

### AI-Powered Performance Support
AI is enabling a new generation of 
performance support tools that go 
beyond static job aids:
- Intelligent assistants that respond 
  to the specific situation
- Real-time coaching during task execution
- Adaptive prompts based on the 
  learner's current performance level

This represents one of the most significant 
shifts in how behavior change interventions 
can be designed — moving from pull 
(learner seeks the resource) to push 
(the resource appears at the moment of need).

